    "popocatepetl_population_exposure": "Within a 100km radius of the Popocatépetl crater live approximately 25 million people, making it one of the most densely populated volcanic risk zones globally. The volcano is currently (as of April/May 2026) at Amarillo Fase 2 with ongoing daily exhalations (e.g., 167 exhalaciones on April 28, 2026). This persistent low-level activity means Popocatépetl-related crisis tweets are a near-continuous presence in the target deployment's tweet stream, not just spike events — a structural difference from the benchmark's event-triggered collection model. Sources: Milenio semáforo explainer — [|https://www.milenio.com/estados/que-es-el-semaforo-de-alerta-volcanica-y-como-funciona|]; Infobae April 2026 monitoring report — [|https://www.infobae.com/mexico/2026/04/29/popocatepetl-tuvo-167-emisiones-este-28-de-abril/|]",
